lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4857  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: Immuno-gold labeling of γCaMKII (CAMK2G) in the dendritic shaft is near postsynaptic synapses of cultured hippocampal neurons. Following stimulation with 30 μmol/L NMDA, co-localization of CAMK2G and PSD95 (DLG4) is increased.\n\n\"A remarkable feature of γCaMKII expression is that it is highly enriched in inhibitory interneurons (e.g., parvalbumin-positive neurons), with relatively fewer excitatory neurons in the hippocampus and cortex (PMID:33548174).\"\nAuthors used immunofluorescence imaging to corroborate this by co-staining alpha- and gamma-CaMKII in cultured hippocampal neurons, and observed: \"We found strong expression of γCaMKII in αCaMKII-negative neurons, which had few spines and were likely interneurons (Fig. 3C, D)\".. Experimental description: MYM: \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from Sprague-Dawley rat pups at postnatal days 0-1.\"\n\nantibody / target sequence:\nrabbit anti-γCaMKII antibody (1:500, ab01)\n\nrat γCaMKII shRNA sequence (5'-TGGCCTGGCCATCGAAGTGCA-3') was subcloned into the pLVTHM vector (12247, Addgene, Watertown, USA) following the manufacturers' protocol." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4857" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

